```typescript
const PROCESSING_FEE = 5;
const FIRST_INSURANCE_RATE = 0.1;

const BASE_PREMIUM: Record<string, number> = {
  sword: 100,
  amulet: 60,
  staff: 80,
  potion: 40,
  rune: 25,
  moonstone: 25,
};

function calculateQuotePremium(items: any[]): number {
  const totalBasePremium = items.reduce(
    (sum: number, item: any) => sum + (BASE_PREMIUM[item.type] ?? 0),
    0,
  );

  const firstInsurance = totalBasePremium * FIRST_INSURANCE_RATE;
  return Math.ceil(totalBasePremium + firstInsurance + PROCESSING_FEE);
}

export function processScenario(scenario: any): unknown {
  const results = scenario.steps.map((step: any) => ({
    premium: calculateQuotePremium(step.items),
  }));

  return { results };
}
```

The block discount rule: components (rune, moonstone) that have exactly 3 of the same type get a special base premium of 60 G instead of 75 G (3 * 25). The block requires exactly 3 alike components.

Minimal approach: in calculateQuotePremium, count components by type. If a component type has exactly 3, use 60 instead of 75. Otherwise use count * 25.

Keep it minimal — only handle the case the test demands.

EXPERIMENT MODE: Run autonomously, proceed to Refactor after completion.

